name: SourceType
notes: Identifies whether the source database is a continuum-operated HMIS (1), an agency-specific database (2), a data warehouse (3), or other (4). An HMIS instance operated jointly by more    than one continuum should be identified as a data warehouse when the CoC export parameter is not used to limit the export to a single CoC.

name: SourceID
notes: If SourceType = 1, this field may not be null and must identify the HUD CoC Code of the HMIS implementation from which data are being exported in the format of two letters, a dash, and 3 numbers. ^[a-zA-Z]{2}-[0-9]{3}$ If SourceType <> 1, this field may be null or used to specify other characteristics, as agreed upon by sender and receiver.

name: SourceName
notes: If the source database is not an HMIS implementation (if SourceType <> 1), this field may not be null and must identify the organization responsible for the database.

name: SourceContactFirst
notes: The first name of the user generating the export.

name: SourceContactLast
notes: The last name of the user generating the export.

name: SourceContactPhone
notes: The phone number of the user generating the export. Limited to 10 digits/no punctuation. [2-9][0-9]{2}[2-9][0-9]{2}[0-9]{4}

name: SourceContactExtension
notes: The phone extension of the user generating the export, if available. Limited to 5 digits/no punctuation. [0-9]{1,5}

name: SourceContactEmail
notes: The email address of the user generating the export, if available. Valid email addresses only

name: ExportDate
notes: The date and time that the export process was initiated.

name: ExportStartDate
notes: The user-entered start date for the export period.

name: ExportEndDate
notes: The user-entered end date for the export period; the ExportEnd should be the same as the ExportStart for exports of HIC data.

name: SoftwareName
notes: The name of the software generating the export.

name: SoftwareVersion
notes: The version number of the software, if applicable.

name: CSVVersion
notes: The version number of the CSV Specification, if aApplicable. This may, but is not required to be, include the [year] and [version].

name: ImplementationID
notes: A vendor-generated ID that is unique to every source database, regardless of the number of CoCs participating in the implementation.

name: UserFirstName
notes: The first name of the user if available

name: UserLastName
notes: The last name of the user if available

name: UserPhone
notes: The phone number of the user if available. Limited to 10 digits/no punctuation. [2-9][0-9]{2}[2-9][0-9]{2}[0-9]{4}

name: UserExtension
notes: The phone extension of the user, if available. Limited to 5 digits/no punctuation. [0-9]{1,5}

name: UserEmail
notes: The email address of the user, if available. Valid email addresses only
